{
  "answer": "**Manusmṛti (also known as the Laws of Manu), Chapter 7.**\n\nThis chapter on the duties of kings personifies *Daṇḍa* (the rod of punishment) precisely as described: the Lord created it as \"his own son ... as Dharma\" at the beginning.[^1] It further warns that without the proper application of punishment by the king, \"the stronger would roast the weaker like fish on a spit.\"[^2]\n\n[^1]: Manusmṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/07/translation/#p-73f910).\n[^2]: Manusmṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/07/translation/#p-d56424).",
